There's a sensor attached to
the bottom of the tape measure.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.335
It'll beep when we hit water.

05:36.628 --> 05:39.006
So, tell me something,
can you tell

05:39.048 --> 05:41.175
how much water
a specific farmer's well

05:41.216 --> 05:43.260
- has dug out of the ground?
- I might

05:43.302 --> 05:44.928
be able to come up
with a rough estimate.

05:44.970 --> 05:46.346
But it would just be a guess.

05:46.388 --> 05:47.598
(BEEPING)

05:47.639 --> 05:49.600
Ah. Here we go.

05:49.641 --> 05:51.101
(EXHALES)

05:51.143 --> 05:53.979
We're down eight feet
since last month.

05:54.021 --> 05:55.981
How bad is that?

05:56.023 --> 05:57.066
Bad-bad.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.942
Historic low.

05:58.984 --> 06:00.944
I know what you need.

06:00.986 --> 06:02.362
But I can't assign
an exact number

06:02.404 --> 06:05.115
to a specific farmer's well.

06:05.157 --> 06:06.867
I'm just trying to find out

06:06.909 --> 06:08.702
if somebody stole
my client's water.

06:08.744 --> 06:11.872
Mm. Water underneath the land
doesn't belong to anyone.

06:11.914 --> 06:15.626
If you can get a drill down
to it, it's yours.

06:16.668 --> 06:19.379
Guess my only other shot is...

06:19.421 --> 06:23.425
try to prove unreasonable use.

06:23.467 --> 06:25.427
Let me put it to you this way:

06:25.469 --> 06:27.346
the corporate farmers
in this area

06:27.387 --> 06:30.099
use more water
than the entire city of L.A.,

06:30.140 --> 06:31.517
which is fucked up

06:31.558 --> 06:34.728
and entirely unreasonable,
in my opinion.

06:34.770 --> 06:36.480
Okay. I appreciate it.

06:36.522 --> 06:38.607
Thanks.

06:40.776 --> 06:43.195
(INSECTS TRILLING)

06:45.864 --> 06:47.741
Hey. I'm almost there.
What's up?

06:47.783 --> 06:49.910
BILLY: So,
I talked to Dr. Mindy from the U.S.

06:49.952 --> 06:52.496
Geological Survey,
and I don't think we can pin

06:52.538 --> 06:54.832
the water problem
on any of Gene's neighbors.

06:54.873 --> 06:56.291
Okay, so we... so we don't have

06:56.333 --> 06:57.459
a wrongful death case.

06:57.501 --> 06:58.794
Well, we could build a case

06:58.836 --> 07:00.796
around reasonable use.

07:00.838 --> 07:03.423
You know, corporate farming
at this scale during

07:03.465 --> 07:05.175
a drought is unreasonable.

07:05.217 --> 07:07.177
That's... No.
That's a trash box idea.

07:07.219 --> 07:08.387
- No.
- Yeah.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.305
We'll know more
once you get the information

07:10.347 --> 07:12.141
- from the water board.
- (SIGHS) All right.

07:12.182 --> 07:13.725
So, uh, what do we need?
We need

07:13.767 --> 07:15.227
drilling permits,
board meeting minutes,

07:15.269 --> 07:17.563
uh, distribution docs.
What else? What else?

07:17.604 --> 07:19.064
And whatever you can get.

07:19.106 --> 07:21.233
Also, thank you for sending me

07:21.275 --> 07:24.069
to such a lush, uh,
and vibrant landscape.

07:24.111 --> 07:26.071
I am literally surrounded
by culture.

07:26.113 --> 07:28.073
So, you're the fucking best.

07:28.115 --> 07:30.242
So, thank you.

07:30.284 --> 07:32.161
Fuck am I?

07:32.202 --> 07:34.288
Goddamn it.

07:42.546 --> 07:43.505
(GASPS)

07:43.547 --> 07:44.673
Fuck!

07:44.715 --> 07:45.924
