09:08.131 --> 09:10.425
(EXHALES)
Yeah, it looks good.

09:10.467 --> 09:12.844
I think we did a good job.

09:12.886 --> 09:15.097
Yeah, the stripes
really bring out the...

09:15.138 --> 09:17.349
beige in the wood.

09:17.391 --> 09:18.350
Hey, girls.

09:18.392 --> 09:19.559
DENISE: Hey.

09:19.601 --> 09:20.727
Hey.

09:20.769 --> 09:22.354
So, what do we do?

09:22.396 --> 09:24.022
Where do we get started?

09:24.064 --> 09:26.024
DENISE: We're done.

09:26.066 --> 09:27.818
- You're three hours late.
- I'm not three hours late.

09:27.859 --> 09:29.403
- DENISE: Three and a half.
- Four hours.

09:29.444 --> 09:31.613
Yeah, like,
three and a half hours late.

09:31.655 --> 09:34.032
Well, thanks for coming by
to help out, Brittany.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.285
And, um, sorry about that.

09:36.326 --> 09:38.328
- What's that?
- Oh, it's a bunch

09:38.370 --> 09:40.455
of almond products.

09:41.832 --> 09:44.793
And here's
some standard oranges.

09:44.835 --> 09:46.545
And if you ever want to be a...

09:46.586 --> 09:48.463
Blackwood Almond Company
ambassador,

09:48.505 --> 09:50.048
make a little extra cash

09:50.090 --> 09:52.050
on the campus here,
I can set you up.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.428
Thanks, but I think I'll pass.

09:54.469 --> 09:55.429
(CHUCKLES)

09:55.470 --> 09:58.974
So, um... anything else?

09:59.016 --> 10:01.310
No, I think
I got it all handled here.

10:01.351 --> 10:03.729
Yeah? All right.

10:03.770 --> 10:06.231
Well, this is 700 bucks.

10:06.273 --> 10:08.317
And that's for emergency snacks

10:08.358 --> 10:09.735
- and whatnot, okay?
- Mm-hmm.

10:09.776 --> 10:12.821
Not fancy, sparkly boots
or something like that.

10:12.863 --> 10:14.781
Who needs to sell almonds,

10:14.823 --> 10:16.491
- am I right?
- Mm-hmm.

10:16.533 --> 10:18.910
Thanks for the education.

10:18.952 --> 10:20.329
You're welcome.

10:20.370 --> 10:22.914
You just make it stick, okay?

10:22.956 --> 10:25.167
BRITTANY: So,

10:25.208 --> 10:26.585
how's it been going with you?

10:26.626 --> 10:28.045
Oh, God, all kind
of exciting things.

10:28.086 --> 10:29.463
I joined Cirque du Soleil.

10:29.504 --> 10:31.006
- Mm.
- Yeah.

10:31.048 --> 10:32.674
(BRITTANY CHUCKLES)

10:32.716 --> 10:35.886
Oh, you know, same old shit.

10:35.927 --> 10:39.306
Well, I've been seeing posters
of Marisol Silva everywhere.

10:39.348 --> 10:40.599
Yeah.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.225
Drives me fucking crazy.

10:42.267 --> 10:44.353
Can't imagine what it must
be like for you.

10:44.394 --> 10:47.731
I try not to think about it.

10:47.773 --> 10:50.484
How's that working out?

10:50.525 --> 10:52.986
Come on, honey, you don't have
to worry about me, all right?

10:53.028 --> 10:55.238
- I'm fine.
- Okay.

10:57.991 --> 11:01.995
I think I'm better off alone,
anyway.

11:02.037 --> 11:04.122
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

11:04.164 --> 11:07.167
Sometimes other people aren't
what you need, right?

11:07.209 --> 11:09.461
Exactly.

