For Gene?

35:48.063 --> 35:50.524
Mother Nature's to blame.

35:50.566 --> 35:52.985
So that's it, then?
Just the drought.

35:55.654 --> 35:57.906
Mm-hmm.

35:59.241 --> 36:01.034
(QUIETLY): Huh.

36:01.076 --> 36:04.413
It's not the drilling that's
going on around here at night?

36:04.454 --> 36:08.208
That's the way we beat the heat
around here, that drilling.

36:08.250 --> 36:11.753
I don't want my workers
dropping dead from heatstroke.

36:11.795 --> 36:14.006
No, no.
I certainly understand that.

36:15.716 --> 36:19.678
But, now, Wheeler, he's...
he's on the water board, right?

36:21.305 --> 36:23.932
- Mm-hmm.
- Wonder why he'd say

36:23.974 --> 36:26.184
- something like that. Oh, hang on a sec.
- (PHONE VIBRATING)

36:30.898 --> 36:33.901
Oh, Wade, this is my daughter.
I got to take it.

36:34.943 --> 36:36.987
Family first.

36:37.029 --> 36:38.530
Hey, honey.

36:38.572 --> 36:41.283
Jesus, Dad,
I thought you were dead.

36:41.325 --> 36:42.784
What?

36:42.826 --> 36:46.330
You left me a voice mail
at 4:00 a.m.

36:46.371 --> 36:48.999
Something about...
writing on the walls and...

36:49.041 --> 36:51.001
how you thought
you were gonna die

36:51.043 --> 36:53.337
and how you wanted me to know
that you loved me.

36:54.421 --> 36:55.923
Do you not remember calling me?

36:55.964 --> 36:57.382
I-I don't know, honey.

36:57.424 --> 36:59.384
- Maybe I was just tired.
- All right, well,

36:59.426 --> 37:00.719
I'm gonna send you the message

37:00.761 --> 37:02.638
'cause it scared
the shit out of me.

37:02.679 --> 37:05.140
(SNIFFS)
Are you okay?

37:05.182 --> 37:06.642
Yeah, I-I'm fine.

37:06.683 --> 37:08.810
I'm sorry I scared you, honey.

37:10.228 --> 37:11.855
Please don't do it again.

37:11.897 --> 37:13.148
Okay.

37:13.190 --> 37:15.359
How about you?
Is everything okay?

37:15.400 --> 37:17.903
My roommate snores.

37:17.945 --> 37:20.155
Look, I...

37:20.197 --> 37:24.117
I got to get to class,
so just...

37:24.159 --> 37:27.037
I'm glad you're not dead.

37:27.079 --> 37:29.206
You just don't worry.
Go on to class.

37:29.247 --> 37:31.249
Check in with me later.

37:34.044 --> 37:36.922
- WOMAN (LAUGHS): 11!
- What?

37:36.964 --> 37:38.256
I...

37:38.298 --> 37:41.343
I played your number, 11,
and I won!

37:41.385 --> 37:42.886
Oh, good. Good.

37:42.928 --> 37:44.763
That's great. I'm gonna
get back in this meeting,

37:44.805 --> 37:46.723
but you have a fun day today,
will you?

37:46.765 --> 37:48.350
- Okay.
- Okay.

38:04.282 --> 38:06.702
(WOMAN SPEAKING OVER RADIO
INDISTINCTLY)

38:13.291 --> 38:14.751
(KNOCKING)

38:16.044 --> 38:17.796
Hey.

38:17.838 --> 38:19.881
I'm so happy you came.

38:19.923 --> 38:22.384
- (SIGHS)
- (CHUCKLES): Come in, come in.

38:22.426 --> 38:25.053
I was just making a cup of tea.

38:25.095 --> 38:27.097
Would you like some?

38:27.139 --> 38:28.724
DELORES: Okay.

38:29.725 --> 38:31.560
JT: Okay.

38:34.354 --> 38:37.566
- I'm glad you're here.
- I'll be in so much trouble

38:37.607 --> 38:40.318
if they know I took this
out of the office.

38:40.360 --> 38:43.530
Delores, I promise you,
nobody's gonna find out.

38:43.572 --> 38:46.074
You don't understand.
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

38:46.116 --> 38:49.119
Someone, somewhere
is always watching.

38:49.161 --> 38:52.164
Then we're gonna have
to be extra careful.

38:53.206 --> 38:54.916
May I?

39:00.672 --> 39:02.174
Thank you.

39:11.058 --> 39:13.435
(TAKES DEEP BREATH)

39:17.939 --> 39:20.901
I'm gonna take this one file
out of the binder.

39:20.942 --> 39:22.944
Are you okay with that?

39:24.196 --> 39:26.531
You take nothing for granted.

39:29.451 --> 39:32.412
I feel terrible about
what happened to Bobbi Bennett.

39:32.454 --> 39:35.165
- Yeah.
- She was so nice.

39:35.207 --> 39:37.167
Well...

39:37.209 --> 39:39.836
this is really
gonna help her case.

39:46.218 --> 39:48.595
- (LOUD BANG)
- (GASPS) What was that?

39:48.637 --> 39:51.223
- (TEAKETTLE WHISTLING)
- I don't know.

39:53.058 --> 39:56.269
- Oh! Jesus! - Oh! (GASPS)
- (CAWING)

39:56.311 --> 39:59.481
Get out! Get out!
Get out! Get out!

39:59.523 --> 40:01.233
Get!

40:01.274 --> 40:04.069
- Get out!
- (DELORES WHIMPERS)

40:04.111 --> 40:05.779
Get out!

40:05.821 --> 40:07.989
- (TEAKETTLE CONTINUES WHISTLING)
- It's okay. It's gone.

40:08.031 --> 40:10.408
- No. No, it's a sign.
- No, no, it's...

40:10.450 --> 40:12.869
I knew this was bad.
I shouldn't have done this.

40:12.911 --> 40:15.080
No, no, you-you...
you're overreacting.

40:15.122 --> 40:17.040
(CHUCKLES): It's a bird.

40:17.082 --> 40:19.042
A bird that flew into the...

40:19.084 --> 40:21.211
It's...

40:21.253 --> 40:23.672
Delores, it's okay!

40:25.382 --> 40:27.467
(TEAKETTLE CONTINUES WHISTLING)

40:30.303 --> 40:32.305
(WHISTLING SLOWLY STOPS)

40:39.521 --> 40:40.981
(EXHALES)

40:42.649 --> 40:44.609
JT: Billy, you remember

40:44.651 --> 40:46.903
- the late '80s?
- I sure do.

40:46.945 --> 40:49.281
Patty, you may be
too young for this.

40:49.322 --> 40:51.408
I absolutely am, yep.

40:51.449 --> 40:54.619
We had a six-year drought
in California.

40:54.661 --> 40:57.122
BILLY: Yeah,
they told us to take a shower

40:57.164 --> 40:59.291
- with a friend. Remember that?
- Come on.

40:59.332 --> 41:00.876
- And we did.
- Why?

41:00.917 --> 41:02.335
Because it was fun.

41:02.377 --> 41:03.837
It was... fun.

41:03.879 --> 41:05.672
Anyway, because of the drought,

41:05.714 --> 41:08.216
the Department
of Water Resources decided

41:08.258 --> 41:11.094
to cut back...
on the ranchers' water,

41:11.136 --> 41:13.138
giving preference
to the residential use.

41:13.180 --> 41:14.264
PATTY: That makes sense.

41:14.306 --> 41:15.473
Yeah.

41:15.515 --> 41:17.058
Only when it happened again,

41:17.100 --> 41:19.186
the ranchers threatened
to sue the state.

41:19.227 --> 41:22.564
Only instead of going to court,

41:22.606 --> 41:26.026
they arranged for a secret,
closed-door meeting

41:26.067 --> 41:27.819
with the Department
of Water Resources

41:27.861 --> 41:31.573
and L.A.'s Metropolitan
Water District...

41:31.615 --> 41:33.575
- in Big Sur.
- BILLY: Big Sur.

41:33.617 --> 41:35.076
Yes, sir.

41:35.118 --> 41:36.578
Yes, sir. Big Sur.

41:36.620 --> 41:39.831
Because of this secret
Big Sur agreement, in exchange

41:39.873 --> 41:42.751
for cutting the ranchers' water
during the drought,

41:42.792 --> 41:45.253
these sneaky shits,

41:45.295 --> 41:48.215
these little douchebag ranchers
managed

41:48.256 --> 41:50.508
to get the state
to give them total control

41:50.550 --> 41:52.928
of the state's water bank.

41:52.969 --> 41:54.512
What's a water bank?

41:54.554 --> 41:56.097
BILLY: It's an underground reservoir.

41:56.139 --> 41:58.934
The state uses it
to store surplus water

41:58.975 --> 42:01.311
when it actually fucking rains.

42:01.353 --> 42:03.521
- How do you know that?
- I read Delores's pamphlet.

42:03.563 --> 42:05.273
Very cool.

42:05.315 --> 42:08.526
Delores. Delores.

42:09.527 --> 42:11.529
She's a really sweet lady.

42:12.781 --> 42:15.116
Billy,
I promised to protect her.

42:15.158 --> 42:17.744
I get it.

42:17.786 --> 42:19.913
WOMAN: Freshen those up?

42:19.955 --> 42:21.748
Yeah.

42:21.790 --> 42:24.084
So you're the lawyers
who are gonna help us,

42:24.125 --> 42:25.669
uh, with this water situation.

42:25.710 --> 42:27.295
PATTY: Yeah.

42:27.337 --> 42:29.631
Oh. Violet mentioned you.

42:29.673 --> 42:32.759
I'm, uh, Gloria, her girlfriend.

42:32.801 --> 42:36.721
I just want to say that I'm glad
someone's looking out for us.

42:41.017 --> 42:43.311
That's nice.

42:43.353 --> 42:45.105
(SIGHS)
So, essentially,

42:45.146 --> 42:48.566
this Big Sur agreement just
gives the ranchers the ability

42:48.608 --> 42:51.069
to use a public resource
to fill their own pockets.

42:51.111 --> 42:53.613
While everyone in town
doesn't have water.

42:53.655 --> 42:55.949
- Yeah.
- Well, if we can prove that

42:55.991 --> 42:57.867
they're distributing water
unfairly,

42:57.909 --> 43:00.370
we can turn Gene's case
into a class action suit.

43:00.412 --> 43:01.913
Yeah.

43:01.955 --> 43:06.459
Well, I got to get these papers
back to Delores, but, uh...

43:06.501 --> 43:08.461
you know,
I'll-I'll put together a list

43:08.503 --> 43:10.255
of what companies
are getting the water.

43:10.297 --> 43:13.049
There's-there's a lot
to dig through here, but...

43:16.720 --> 43:18.680
GENE: What?

43:18.722 --> 43:21.766
Yeah, I know. I kn...

43:21.808 --> 43:23.560
Oh, you know
who called the other day?

43:23.601 --> 43:27.605
Tim Kovac.
Remember him? UT Austin?

43:27.647 --> 43:30.191
You know, he's still pitching

43:30.233 --> 43:33.111
that goddamn rhetoric manuscript
of his.

43:33.153 --> 43:35.280
It's... Well,
now he's got a new title.

43:35.322 --> 43:36.698
Wait. Wait for it.

43:36.740 --> 43:39.409
It's called, um... Oh, God.

43:39.451 --> 43:42.370
That's So Punny:

43:42.412 --> 43:46.166
Turgidity in Romance Languages.

43:46.207 --> 43:48.001
Hmm?
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

43:48.043 --> 43:49.711
No, I said I would read it.

43:49.753 --> 43:51.796
I mean,
that's professional courtesy.

43:51.838 --> 43:53.590
Yeah.

43:53.631 --> 43:56.259
- Why, he reads my stuff, I read his stuff, you know.
- (KNOCKING)

43:56.301 --> 43:58.303
- Gene?
- What?

44:00.472 --> 44:02.265
I...

44:02.307 --> 44:04.434
I don't...
I don't understand.

44:04.476 --> 44:07.020
Well, this way,
we take your case,

44:07.062 --> 44:09.397
and we roll it
into a class action lawsuit.

44:09.439 --> 44:11.691
We have a hell
of a lot better chance this way.

44:11.733 --> 44:14.235
PATTY: It's power in numbers.

44:15.820 --> 44:17.489
But what about Bobbi?

44:17.530 --> 44:19.657
PATTY: Well, there'd be no separate

44:19.699 --> 44:21.076
wrongful death claim.

44:21.117 --> 44:22.744
Your pain and suffering
would be part

44:22.786 --> 44:25.372
of the class action lawsuit.

44:25.413 --> 44:27.415
My pain and suffering

44:27.457 --> 44:29.459
isn't like everyone else's,

44:29.501 --> 44:31.461
'cause my wife is dead.

44:31.503 --> 44:33.630
- BILLY: Yeah.
- My wife is dead, you got that?

44:33.671 --> 44:35.840
- PATTY: Yeah.
- Well, see,

44:35.882 --> 44:38.802
doing it like this,
we can get you compensation,

44:38.843 --> 44:42.514
and you can have some closure
on Bobbi's death.

44:46.643 --> 44:48.937
Right. (STAMMERS)

44:50.313 --> 44:53.149
If you want to hit them
where it hurts,

44:53.191 --> 44:55.819
then this is absolutely the way
to do it.

44:57.445 --> 45:00.490
We really need you
on board here, Gene.

45:00.532 --> 45:03.952
As a matter of fact,
uh, I think we may be able

45:03.993 --> 45:06.037
to shut 'em down altogether.

45:07.455 --> 45:10.166
Well, that's what Bobbi
really wanted.

45:18.341 --> 45:20.301
PATTY: Thank you.

45:20.343 --> 45:22.554
- Arm?
- (SIGHS)

45:22.595 --> 45:24.389
(GASPS)
Jesus Christ.

45:24.431 --> 45:26.516
- Sorry, honey.
- (SIGHS)

45:26.558 --> 45:29.018
So are you... are you heading
back, or you staying here?

45:29.060 --> 45:31.062
- What are you doing?
- Well, to tell you the truth,

45:31.104 --> 45:34.232
I'm kind of used
to the casino at this point.

45:34.274 --> 45:36.609
Why don't you want
to go back to L.A.?

45:38.987 --> 45:41.698
I don't know. You know, Denise
is settled in at college,

45:41.739 --> 45:45.452
and... I don't really need
that fucking place in Venice.

45:45.493 --> 45:47.454
You gonna sell it?

45:47.495 --> 45:49.622
- I've been thinking about it.
- You know I can move that.

45:49.664 --> 45:52.167
- You know I can move that.
- (LAUGHING): I know.

45:52.208 --> 45:54.210
I am very expensive, however.

45:54.252 --> 45:57.297
- I can pay.
- I know.

45:57.338 --> 45:59.966
(INSECTS TRILLING)

46:00.008 --> 46:02.218
Do I need to be
worried about you?

46:05.597 --> 46:07.724
You get home safe, honey.

46:12.353 --> 46:14.522
Hey.

46:22.280 --> 46:24.324
(COINS CLINKING)

46:35.001 --> 46:37.420
(SLOT MACHINE CHIMING)

46:37.462 --> 46:38.505
Here you go.

46:38.546 --> 46:40.381
- Oh, thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

47:05.823 --> 47:07.867
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:37.188 --> 47:39.274
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:49.993 --> 47:51.536
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

48:20.732 --> 48:22.734
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:34.954 --> 48:36.956
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:53.640 --> 48:55.725
(CROW CAWING)

49:07.779 --> 49:09.614
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

49:12.367 --> 49:14.369
(BILLY SIGHS)

49:16.954 --> 49:18.956
Wade.

49:20.583 --> 49:23.670
You were a little loose
with your facts.

49:25.588 --> 49:27.757
Really? How's that?

49:27.799 --> 49:29.759
Well, you're the president
of the water board.

49:29.801 --> 49:31.427
Mm-hmm.

49:31.469 --> 49:33.805
Responsible for distribution
of water in the county,

49:33.846 --> 49:35.890
and you rigged the system.

49:35.932 --> 49:38.059
- I did?
- Yes, sir.

49:38.101 --> 49:40.061
How's that?

49:40.103 --> 49:42.939
Well, on paper,
it looks like you get 12%.

49:42.980 --> 49:44.774
But in reality,

49:44.816 --> 49:48.069
through a bunch of
shell corporations, you get 75.

49:49.696 --> 49:52.115
Ah, shoot. You caught me.

49:53.825 --> 49:56.035
And I wasn't even hiding.

49:56.077 --> 49:58.621
I asked you
about the water board.

49:58.663 --> 50:01.290
Yeah, but you didn't ask me
about my business,

50:01.332 --> 50:03.084
and those are
two different hats.

50:03.126 --> 50:06.963
Well, if you weren't hiding,
why the shell corporations?

50:07.004 --> 50:09.048
(SIGHS)

50:09.090 --> 50:12.343
I told you
that I would tell you everything

50:12.385 --> 50:15.430
you wanted to know
about the water board,

50:15.471 --> 50:18.641
as long as it wasn't covered
by the NDA.

50:20.768 --> 50:22.854
So ask me.

50:22.895 --> 50:25.189
You don't give a damn
about the people in town

50:25.231 --> 50:26.816
who don't have a drop of water?

50:26.858 --> 50:28.776
We take very good care
of our employees.

50:28.818 --> 50:33.364
We give them everything
that they need.

50:33.406 --> 50:35.241
But if we don't have water,

50:35.283 --> 50:37.994
we don't have crops,
and they don't have jobs.

50:38.035 --> 50:40.538
- And you don't have millions.
- (SIGHS)

50:42.874 --> 50:46.085
Everything we do here
is perfectly legal.

50:46.127 --> 50:50.465
You want to argue
about the ethics, go ahead.

50:50.506 --> 50:52.842
It won't win you a case
in court.

50:52.884 --> 50:55.178
Yeah. Unless maybe the jurors
don't have any water.

50:55.219 --> 50:56.846
Tell you one thing.

50:56.888 --> 50:59.182
I'm sure as shit gonna sue you
in Blackwood County.

50:59.223 --> 51:00.808
You can bet your ass on that.

51:00.850 --> 51:03.269
Oh. Oh, man.

51:04.771 --> 51:08.191
Oh, man!
That is such a bummer.

51:08.232 --> 51:10.860
And I was just getting
to like you, Billy.

51:10.902 --> 51:13.362
Yeah, back at you, Wade.

51:13.404 --> 51:15.782
Let me ask you something.

51:15.823 --> 51:18.534
If everything
you're doing is perfectly legal,

51:18.576 --> 51:21.204
then, why the NDA?

51:23.289 --> 51:27.043
I can't say.
That's the point.

51:27.084 --> 51:29.295
- Yeah.
- (SIGHS)

51:29.337 --> 51:31.631
Well, I think
you just made mine, too.

51:35.760 --> 51:37.762
(ENGINE STARTS)

51:46.479 --> 51:48.481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

